[2]
Date: 18 May 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AP Online, 18 May 2001, BBC Television, 17 May 2001

London -- For the first time since foot and mouth disease was confirmed in
Britain 3 months ago, no new daily cases were reported [on 17 May]. The
Ministry of Agriculture reported Thursday night no new cases had been
confirmed in England, Scotland and Wales for the day.
The first outbreak of the livestock disease was confirmed on 20 Feb and, at
the epidemic's height in March. as many as 40 new cases were confirmed
daily. The current total [on 17 May] is 1603 cases in Britain and 4
confirmed cases in Northern Ireland. Some 1.3 million cattle and sheep have
been killed in an attempt to halt the spread of the highly contagious disease.
