[3]
Date: Sunday 20 May
From: ProMED-mail<promed@promedmail.org>
Source: MAFF statistics [edited]
<http://www.maff.gov.uk/animalh/diseases/fmd/statistics.htm>

Slaughter/disposal numbers, 20 May 2001
---------------------------------------
Slaughter and disposal statistics are reported as they have been completed
and collated, and there is inevitably a delay to this, given the scale of
operations. These figures are therefore subject to revision.
3 050 000 animals slaughtered or identified as being for slaughter.
2 972 000 animals slaughtered, of which 26 000 remain to be disposed of.
462 000 cattle, 2 390 000 sheep, 118 000 pigs, 2000 goats slaughtered.
78 000 animals awaiting slaughter.
